%I A397058 #11 Jun 19 2026 22:13:43
%S A397058 12,194,342,6000
%N A397058 Integers x such that there exist four integers 0<y<=z<=t<=w such that sigma(x)*psi(x)^3*phi(x) = x^5 + y^5 + z^5 + t^5 + w^5.
%C A397058 The numbers x, y, z, t and w form a sigma*psi^3*phi-quintic quintuple.
%H A397058 S. I. Dimitrov, <a href="https://github.com/Stoyan16/Sigma-psi-3-phi-quintic-quintuples/blob/main/A397058">Python program</a> (GitHub)
%e A397058 (342, 54, 261, 315, 468) is such a quintuple because sigma(342) * psi(342)^3 * phi(342) = 780 * 720^3 * 108 = 342^5 + 54^5 + 261^5 + 315^5 + 468^5. Other quintuples are (12, 4, 4, 12, 16), (194, 19, 37, 83, 213) and (6000, 4320, 5180, 5700, 9400).
%o A397058 (Python) # See Links.
%Y A397058 Cf. A000010, A000203, A001615, A003350, A386672, A390006, A395737.
%K A397058 nonn,hard,more,new
%O A397058 1,1
